choices.text:
why does this command give error Permission denied (publickey):

ssh -i \“~/UserKey.pem" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com
The error "Permission denied (publickey)" indicates that the SSH server is not configured to accept connections from the public key specified in your command. This could be due to a number of reasons, such as incorrect permissions on the private key file or configuration issues with the SSH server. 
To troubleshoot this issue, you may want to verify that the private key file has the correct permissions (chmod 600 ~/UserKey.pem) and ensure that the public IP address of your instance is correctly specified in the command. Additionally, you can check the security group settings for the instance to make sure that SSH access is enabled and the appropriate rules are in place.
